    "wikipediaUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compass_Pathways",
    "extract": "Compass Pathways, or COMPASS Pathways, is a British pharmaceutical company developing psychedelics as potential medicines. Its main drug candidate, psilocybin (COMP360), has completed phase 3 clinical trials for treatment-resistant depression. The results showed clear benefit to participants as measured on the MADRS depression rating scale. This candidate has received breakthrough therapy status from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA). It is the most advanced psychedelic drug candidate in development besides Lykos Therapeutics's midomafetamine (MDMA)."
